Illinois Tool Works Inc Reaffirms Q4 2011 And FY 2011 Guidance
Monday, 19 Dec 2011 08:00am EST
Illinois Tool Works Inc announced that for the fourth quarter of 2011, it expects diluted income per share (EPS) from continuing operations to be in a range of $0.86 to $0.94 and total revenue growth range of 9.5% to 12.5%. For fiscal 2011, the Company is forecasting diluted income per share from continuing operations to be in a range of $4.04 to $4.12 and assumes a total revenue growth range of 15.1% to 15.9%. The fiscal 2011 forecast includes the $0.33 per share one-time tax benefit recorded in the 2011 first quarter. Excluding the one-time tax gain, the midpoint of the full-year earnings would be $3.75. The Company reported revenue of $15.870 billion in fiscal 2010. According to I/B/E/S Estimates, analysts were expecting the Company to report EPS of $0.89 on revenues of $4.38 billion for the fourth quarter of 2011; and revenues of $17.89 billion for fiscal 2011.Â 
